\f2 Tools for MVVM: bindings, @ObservedObject and Combine\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Model-View-ViewModel (MVVM) is a software architectural pattern or design pattern, which is a way to organize your code better. It\'92s organized around 3 roles: Models, Views and ViewModels. A special place is reserved for bindings.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f3 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\b Model:
\f2\b0 \'a0A model is a representation of data. They are the bits and bytes your app moves around, from tweets to User objects to to-do list tasks.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f3 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\b View:
\f2\b0 \'a0A view is responsible for displaying data to the user of your app, and handling interaction. It\'92s the UI of your app, or part of it.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f3 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\b ViewModel:
\f2\b0 \'a0A ViewModel represents the state of model data. It facilitates communication between views and models, through bindings, or other events and actions.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0
\f3 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\b Bindings:
\f2\b0 \'a0A binding isn\'92t exactly a role, but it\'92s a central part of MVVM. Think of a binding as a connection between a piece of data and the view that displays or manipulates it.\
